cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.DS 

The paper deals with the problem of predicting commodity arrivals in agriculture using remote sensing data and short time-series. This involves dealing with high-dimensional data and using regression models for prediction. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves using historical data and short-term prediction of important variables, which suggests the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The use of remote sensing data suggests the sub-category cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). The paper also involves using regression models, which suggests the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves dealing with high-dimensional data, which suggests the sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
